b'' b'from the article "what\'s new" apr-16-93 in sci.physics.research:' b'' b'........' b"what's new (in my opinion), friday, april washington, dc" b'' b'1. space billboards! is this one the "spinoffs" we were promised?' b'in science fiction writer robert heinlein published "the' b'man who sold the moon," which involved a dispute over the sale of' b'rights to the moon for use as billboard. nasa has taken the firsteps toward this' b'hideous vision of the future. observers were' b'startled this spring when a nasa launch vehicle arrived at the' b'pad with "schwarzenegger" painted in huge block letters on the' b'side of the booster rockets. space marketing inc. had arranged' b"for the ad to promote arnold's latest movie. now, space marketing" b'is working with university of colorado and livermore engineers on' b'a plan to place a mile-long inflatable billboard in low-earth' b'orbit. nasa would provide contractual launch services. however,' b'since nasa bases its charge on seriously flawed cost estimates' b'(wn mar the taxpayers would bear most of the expense. this' b'may look like environmental vandalism, but mike lawson, ceo of' b'space marketing, told us yesterday that the real purpose of the' b'project is to help the environment! the platform will carry ozone' b'monitors he explained--advertising is just to help defray costs.' b'..........' b'' b'what do you think of this revolting and hideous attempt to vandalize' b'the night sky? it is not even april anymore.' b'what about light pollution in observations? (i read somewhere else that' b'it might even be visible during the day, leave alone at night).' b'is nasa really supporting this junk?' b'are protesting groups being organized in the states?' b'really, really depressed.' b'' b'enzo' b'--' b'canon information systems research australia phone b'po box north ryde nsw fax 